      "content": "\"Their very constitution betrays their limitations; they possess the brute strength for labor, certainly, but lack the refined mental architecture for self-direction. They are built for the plow and the command, not for the delicate machinations of governance. A strong hand, a guiding intellect like our own, is not an imposition, but a natural complement to their inherent disposition. They require a shepherd, for their nature is too easily led toward the productive and the orderly.\"",
